Unfortunately due to the continued Covid-19 pandemic and current social distancing guidelines from the state and school, we will be cancelling fall sports for the 2020 season. No decision has been made about winter or spring sports yet and information will be shared as soon as it is available.

We are very sorry for the athletes and families that were looking forward to this season and we hope to get athletics up and running as soon as we can.

You can contact Mr. Horton at horton@horizoncleveland.org with any questions or concerns.

post_text:
On Saturday, March 7, 2020 SFC DeJesus and his cadets participated in a drill meet at Lincoln-West. The students did an amazing job and ranked high in several categories!

1st year color guard: 1st place
Advanced color guard: 2nd place
Platoon Drill: 2nd place
Academic team: 2nd place
Raider team: 3rd place
Individual Cadet Drill consisted of 150 cadets:
Kayla King 3rd place; Kristian Watts 4th

We are so proud of them and how well they represented our school. Congratulations to all the cadets who participated in this event!

post_text:
Mr. Isa and his Computer students attended an overnight event organized by a non-profit called Execute Big at Gilmour Academy on Feb 29th. Students of all skill levels were engaged in the world of technology and experienced to build innovative solutions. This was an event where around 75 high school students around the greater Cleveland region came together to build apps, games, websites, and programs. Our students had a great time building two websites to find solutions fixing social issues.

Attached are some pictures from the event!

The PEEKE Internship Program (Partnerships, Exploration, Experience, Knowledge, Excellence) is a selective internship program offered to 30 high school sophomores and juniors throughout Cuyahoga County. Applicants who are interested in gaining professional skills and hands-on career exploration while earning a stipend and networking in a career field of their interest are encouraged to apply!

APPLY NOW: https://www.youthopportunities.org/internships

APPLICATION DEADLINE: MONDAY, MARCH 16, 2020 BY NOON.

post_text:
A group of our students have recently applied for the Congressional Award Program from which CYSP was originally inspired. You can view more information about the program here: https://www.congressionalaward.org/

On Sunday, November 10, our students participated in an activity called Mitzvah Project to assemble Overground Railroad Travelers Kits. The event was organized by IRTFCleveland.org. The organization provides help for immigrant families living or travelling through Northeastern Ohio.

Students were given a lesson on the US Immigration history and issues followed by the activity to prepare the traveler kits.

post_text:
The Cleveland Leadership Center is now accepting applications for Accelerate 2020: Citizens Make Change – a civic pitch competition that gives individuals an opportunity to bring their community-focused ideas to life. Anyone with an idea to make Greater Cleveland a better place to work, live, play, or visit can apply. Finalists from each of the categories win $2,000 and the overall winner receives $5,000 to help launch their idea. Ideas that involve technology can win additional funds in the Technovation Competition where the Cleveland Foundation is giving away $3,500 for the top technology idea.

Pitch applications are open until 9:00 a.m. on December 2 at www.cleveleads.org/accelerate.…
shared_text:
CLEVELEADS.ORG
Accelerate - Cleveland Leadership Center
text:
The Cleveland Leadership Center is now accepting applications for Accelerate 2020: Citizens Make Change – a civic pitch competition that gives individuals an opportunity to bring their community-focused ideas to life. Anyone with an idea to make Greater Cleveland a better place to work, live, play, or visit can apply. Finalists from each of the categories win $2,000 and the overall winner receives $5,000 to help launch their idea. Ideas that involve technology can win additional funds in the Technovation Competition where the Cleveland Foundation is giving away $3,500 for the top technology idea.

Pitch applications are open until 9:00 a.m. on December 2 at www.cleveleads.org/accelerate.…

CLEVELEADS.ORG
Accelerate - Cleveland Leadership Center
